<%= turbo_stream_from "clips" %>

<div class="wrapper">

  <header>
    <h1>Web dictaphone</h1>
  </header>

  <div id="main-controls" data-turbo-permanent>
  <section class="main-controls" data-controller="main-controls" data-turbo-permanent>
    <canvas class="visualizer" height="60px"></canvas>
    <div id="buttons">
      <button class="record">Record</button>
      <button class="stop">Stop</button>
    </div>
  </section>
  </div>

  <section class="sound-clips">
  <%= render @clips %>
  </section>

</div>

<label for="toggle">‚ùî</label>
<input type="checkbox" id="toggle">
<aside>
  <h2>Information</h2>

  <p><a href="https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/tree/main/media/web-dictaphone#web-dictaphone">Web dictaphone</a> is built using <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator.getUserMedia">getUserMedia</a> and the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaRecorder_API">MediaRecorder API</a>, which provides an easier way to capture Media streams.</p>

  <p>Icon courtesy of <a href="http://findicons.com/search/microphone">Find Icons</a>. Thanks to <a href="http://soledadpenades.com/">Sole</a> for the Oscilloscope code!</p>

  <hr>

  <p>Rails Dictaphone adds:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><p><a href="https://guides.rubyonrails.org/active_record_basics.html">Active Record</a> with a <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</a> database to persist an ordered list of clips</p></li>
    <li><p><a href="https://edgeguides.rubyonrails.org/active_storage_overview.html">Active Storage</a> with a <a href="https://www.tigrisdata.com/">Tigris</a> bucket for storing audio files</p></li>
    <li><p><a href="https://turbo.hotwired.dev/handbook/streams">Turbo Stream<a> with <a href="https://upstash.com/">Upstash</a> Redis db and <a href=""https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSockets_API">WebSockets</a> for broadcasting updates</a></p></li>
  </ul>

  <p>Multiple replicas of this application can be deployed, even in multiple regions.</p>
</aside>